New Records: De'Aaron Fox now has the most points over a two-game span in Sacramento Kings franchise history, surpassing DeMarcus Cousins.
Key Match Events: De'Aaron Fox scored 49 points to lead the Sacramento Kings to a 121-117 win over the Utah Jazz.
The Jazz opened the third quarter with a 10-3 run and ended the frame with a 94-90 lead.
Sacramento came back in the fourth to take a 118-116 lead on a Jordan McLaughlin 3 with a minute left to play.
Fox made the last two free throws to seal the victory.
Miscellaneous Highlights: De'Aaron Fox scored 60 points in a losing effort the night before.
DeMar DeRozan, Malik Monk, and Domantas Sabonis were sidelined for Sacramento, and Taylor Hendricks and Walker Kessler did not play for the Jazz.
